// E2E tests for cascade message sends
// Cascades send multiple messages to the same receiver using semicolon (;)
//
// SYNTAX: receiver msg1; msg2; msg3
//
// NOTE: Cascade syntax is parsed but code generation is not yet implemented.
// These tests document the intended syntax for future implementation.
//
// Cascades are useful for initialization patterns:
//   collection add: 1; add: 2; add: 3
//   stream write: 'hello'; nl; write: 'world'
//
// The parser recognizes cascade syntax, but the REPL doesn't yet evaluate it.
// See: Expression::Cascade in crates/beamtalk-core/src/ast.rs
